# Copy to /etc/ereport/ecrawl-daily.conf and adjust paths.
# Syntax:
#   - Lines before ---jobs--- are directives: KEY=value
#   - After ---jobs---, one crawl per line, TAB-separated:
#       start_path — directory ecrawl walks
#       output_dir — where crawl output (shards, etc.) is written; empty → ecrawl default beside the tree;
#                    parent dirs are created if missing (mkdir -p)
#       record_root — optional --record-root (logical root in metadata); empty → omit --record-root
#     Empty middle/right columns still need tabs (e.g. path<TAB><TAB>).

ECRAWL_BIN=/opt/ereport/ecrawl
BIN_SOURCE_DIR=/opt/ereport
# Deployment parent on the target: after promotion, ecrawl/ereport/… sit *in this directory*,
# not under a child such as bin/ unless you set RSYNC_DEST to that child path explicitly.
# (So avoid paths that read like an “app prefix” unless you really keep binaries flat there.)
# Flow: rsync → PARENT/.ecrawl-daily-staging/, then that directory's prior contents (except
# archive/ and the staging dir) move to PARENT/archive/<timestamp>/, then staging → PARENT.
RSYNC_DEST=backup.example.com:/opt/ereport-live/
# Optional: remote shell for rsync and ssh promote step (same -e as rsync)
# RSYNC_RSH=ssh -o BatchMode=yes -o StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new
# RSYNC_DELETE=1
# RSYNC_STAGING_DIR_NAME=.ecrawl-daily-staging
# RSYNC_ARCHIVE_DIR_NAME=archive

# --- jobs (TAB-separated: start_path, output_dir, record_root) ---
---jobs---
/mnt/server-a/data	/var/lib/ecrawl/server-a	
/mnt/server-b/home	/var/lib/ecrawl/server-b	/mnt/server-b/home
